title: A nonspeaking valedictorian with autism gives her college's commencement speech - NPR
content: A nonspeaking valedictorian with autism gives her college's commencement speech  NPRView Full Coverage on Google News
description: A computer keyboard "unlocked my mind from its silent cage," Elizabeth Bonker told her fellow graduates. She urged them to serve others, citing Rollins College's most famous alum: Fred Rogers.
